Re-implementation of PredNet: https://coxlab.github.io/prednet/

File structure:

PredNet/
| requirements.txt (Install necessary libraries etc. via: pip install -r requirements.txt)
| setup.py (Convenient way to install every necessary framework/library)
| main.py  (Start/Stop training & testing etc.)
| train.py (Training)
| test.py  (Testing)
| validate.py (Validation)
| README (This readme file)
- data/    (data files and some scripts for fetching and pre-processing)
-- scripts/
--| 00sequences.txt
--| download_kth.sh (from:
--| download_caltech.sh
--| data_utils_kth.py (from:
--| data_utils_caltech.py
--| moving_mnist.py (from:
- datasets/
-| __init__.py
-| Kitti.py
-| MovingMNIST.py
-| Kth.py
-| Caltech.py
- graph/   (.dot-graphs of backprop graph)
- log/     (log of txt-file & tensorboard logs)
- mdl/     (Saving PyTorch models)
- model/   (PredNet model)
-| __init__.py
-| prednet.py
-- modules/ (Simple modules, e.g. LSTM)
--| __init__.py
--| conv_lstm.py
--| input.py
--| prediction.py
--| error.py
-- helper/  (Useful helper, e.g. yml parser)
--| __init__.py
--| arguments.py
--| datetime.py
--| logger.py
--| loss.py
--| mdl.py
--| plot_graph.py
--| tensorboard_log.py
--| transformation.py
--| yaml_parser.py
- yml/     (Hyperparameter)
-| prednet_kitti_l0.yml
-| prednet_kth_l0.yml
-| prednet_mnist_l0.yml

To use the datasets <MovingMNIST|Kitti|KTH|Caltech> one needs to download and preprocess the data. Most download and preprocess scripts are found in data/scripts.
